    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (80.98) standing as our most compelling start. While his #8 spot in the lineup is typically a drain on value, he faces a soft matchup against Roki Sasaki (5.52 xERA) and benefits from favorable wind conditions, providing a massive boost to his ceiling. Joining him at the top of our daily hierarchy are **Junior Caminero** (71.49) and **Trea Turner** (70.15). **Junior Caminero** is particularly well-positioned as he draws a strong platoon advantage against Bailey Ober, and **Trea Turner** maintains his status as an essential anchor, utilizing his lead-off spot to maximize run production despite facing Bryce Elder. **Kyle Schwarber** (66.61) also warrants attention; his elite 0.402 xwOBA makes him a high-floor start regardless of the neutral park factors.\n\nStrategic benching remains critical, especially given our focus on SB efficiency. **Josh Smith** (43.39) was the closest exclusion from the active roster. While his ability to exploit slow SP deliveries makes him a legitimate threat on the basepaths, he ultimately lost out to **Kazuma Okamoto** (52.94), whose superior raw projection and favorable platoon against Joey Cantillo provided a more reliable path to production. Managers should keep a close watch on **Victor Scott II** (38.48); his score remains suppressed by a tough matchup against Bryan Woo and a low lineup position, but he remains our primary contingency if any late-breaking lineup changes occur. \n\nA final note of caution: with nearly our entire lineup labeled \"Lineup Pending,\" the scores for **Gary Sanchez**, **Dillon Dingler**, **Colt Keith**, **Chase Meidroth**, **Luke Raley**, **Yordan Alvarez**, and **Hyeseong Kim** are subject to volatility. Specifically, **Dillon Dingler** carries a dynamic platoon risk that could drag his efficiency further if the official lineup shifts his role. We are monitoring **Christian Yelich**\u2019s recovery from the IL, but for now, he remains unavailable to help anchor our scoring.",
